{{Infobox artwork | title = The Good Fruit of the Earth | painting_alignment = | other_language_1 = Greek | other_title_1 = Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | image = The Good Fruit of the Earth - Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | artist = Lucia Nicolaidou-Vasiliou | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1933}} | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | medium = oil on canvas | material = | subject = | height_metric = 188 <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = 140 | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = <!-- (i.e. in imperial units) --> | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = | city = | museum = State Gallery of Contemporary Cypriot Art | accession = | coordinates = <!-- Only use for the coordinates (when known) of the artwork itself, i.e. not for the site, building, structure, etc where it is kept, otherwise leave blank (or omit): {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | owner = | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = }} '''The Good Fruit of the Earth''' is a painting created by the [[Cyprus|Cypriot]] painter [[Loukia Nicolaidou]] between the years 1933 - 1936.
== Description == The painting, oil on canvas, has dimensions of 188&nbsp;cm. X 140&nbsp;cm<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy/items/show/614|title=Nicolaidou, Loukia (1909-1994), “The Good Fruit of the Earth - Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης”|last=|first=|date=|website=cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy|publisher=Ψηφιακή Πλατφόρμα Κυπριακής Βιβλιοθήκης|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref> and is exhibited at the State Gallery of Contemporary Cypriot Art.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy/items/show/614|title=Nicolaidou, Loukia (1909-1994), “The Good Fruit of the Earth - Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης”|last=|first=|date=|website=cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy|publisher=Ψηφιακή Πλατφόρμα Κυπριακής Βιβλιοθήκης|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>
==Analysis== The painting was made by Lucia Nicolaidou-Vasiliou, the first woman from Cyprus to study painting abroad,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sigmalive.com/archive/simerini/news/social/403696|title=Οχτώ Κύπριες άνοιξαν το δρόμο στις υπόλοιπες|last=Σωφρονίου|first=Ελευθερία|date=23 July 2011|website=sigmalive.com|publisher=Sigma Live|accessdate=21 July 2016}}</ref> particularly in France. In this canvas she demonstrates the obvious influence of [[Paul Gauguin]] as shown in the areas of the forms, the theme and the symbolism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy/items/show/614|title=Nicolaidou, Loukia (1909-1994), “The Good Fruit of the Earth - Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης”|last=|first=|date=|website=cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy|publisher=Ψηφιακή Πλατφόρμα Κυπριακής Βιβλιοθήκης}}</ref> The painting stands out for its large color surfaces and for the female figures mother and daughter, symbolizing the quest for innocence,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy/items/show/614|title=Nicolaidou, Loukia (1909-1994), “The Good Fruit of the Earth - Αγαθοί Καρποί της Γης”|last=|first=|date=|website=cyprusdigitallibrary.org.cy|publisher=Ψηφιακή Πλατφόρμα Κυπριακής Βιβλιοθήκης|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref> while exuding a sense of sensuality absent from the corresponding women depicted in the works of other Cypriot artists of that period.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Η ανθρώπινη μορφή στη νεότερη Κυπριακή τέχνη: οι πρώτες γενιές|last=Δανός|first=Αντώνης|publisher=Ίδρυμα Ευαγόρα Λανίτη & Κάθλην Λανίτη, Υπουργείο Παιδείας και Πολιτισμού.|year=2006|isbn=|location=Κύπρος|page=12}}</ref>
